title.text: data science

note.text:
deals with how computers can be made for gaining high-level understanding from digital images or videos

it seeks to automate tasks that the human visual system can do

title.text: artificial intelligence

note.text: is the study of ‘intelligent agents’ (any device that perceives its environment and takes actions that maximise its chance of success at some goal)

title.text: cryptography

note.text:
practice and study of hiding information, is used to try and keep information secret and safe

note.text:
gives computer the ability to learn without being explicitly programmed

requires good understanding of linear algebra and statistics

title.text: entrepreneurship

note.text: is the process of designing, launching and running a new business, which typically begins as a small business, such as a startup company, offering a product, process or service for sale or hire

title.text: biology

note.text: is concerned with the study of life and living organisms, including their structure, function, growth, evolution, distribution, identification and taxonomy

title.text: game development

note.text:
is the process of creating a video game

first video games were developed in the 1960s, but required mainframe computers and were not available to the general public

title.text: anthropology

note.text: is the study of various aspects of humans within past and present societies

title.text: economics

note.text: is concerned with description and analysis of the production, distribution, and consumption of goods and services

title.text: computer graphics

note.text:
are pictures and films created using computers

it refers to computer-generated image data created with help from specialised graphical hardware and software

helpful to have understanding of linear algebra

title.text: marketing

note.text: is the study and management of exchange relationships

title.text: mathematics

note.text:
study of numbers, shapes and patterns

to a mathematician, the reason something is true is just as important as the fact that it is true

it includes the study of :

numbers (i.e. 3 + 6 = 9)

structure (how things are organised)

place (where things are and their arrangement)

change (how things become different over time)

it uses logic, paper and calculator

a proof gives a reason why a rule in mathematics is correct

sometimes, math finds and studies rules or ideas in the real world that we don’t understand yet

studying the rules and ideas of mathematics can help us understand the world better

title.text: computer science

note.text:
is the study of the theory, experimentation and engineering that form the basis for the design and use of computers

it is the study of automating algorithmic processes that scale

title.text: chemistry

note.text:
is a branch of physical science that studies the composition, structure, properties and change of matter

it includes topics such as the properties of individual atoms, how atoms form chemical bonds to create chemical compounds, the interactions of substances through intermolecular forces that give matter its general properties, and the interactions between substances through chemical reactions to form different substances

title.text: psychology

note.text: is the science of behavior and mind, embracing all aspects of conscious and unconscious experience as well as thought

title.text: health

note.text: is the level of functional and metabolic efficiency of a living organism

title.text: physics

note.text:
is involved with the study of matter and its motion and behaviour through space and time, lagoon with related concepts such as energy and force

its fundamental goal is to understand how the universe behaves

helpful to have understanding of mathematics

title.text: virtual reality

note.text: typically refers to computer technologies that use virtual reality headsets to generate the realistic images, sounds and other sensations that replicate a real environment or create an imaginary setting

title.text: management

note.text: is the administration of an organisation, whether it be a business, a not-for-profit organisation, or government body

title.text: computer networking

note.text:
computer network is a telecommunications network which allows nodes to share resources

in computer networks, networked computing devices exchange data with each other using a data link

title.text: databases

note.text:
are organised collections of data

they are a collection of schemas, tables, queries, reports, views, and other objects

title.text: engineering

note.text: is the application of mathematics and scientific, economic, social, and practical knowledge in order to invent, innovate, design, build, maintain, research, and improve structures, machines, tools, systems, components, materials, processes, solutions, and organizations

title.text: law

note.text: is a system of rules that are created and enforced through social or governmental institutions to regulate behavior

title.text: distributed computing

note.text:
a distributed system is a model in which components located on networked computers communicate and coordinate their actions by passing messages

the components interact with each other in order to achieve a common goal

title.text: history

note.text:
is the study of the past as it is described in written documents

it is best we learn from the mistakes done already so to not repeat them again

title.text: neuroscience

note.text:
is the scientific study of the nervous system

deals with the anatomy, biochemistry, molecular biology, and physiology of neurons and neural circuits

title.text: medicine

title.text: programming

is a process that leads from an original formulation of a computing problem to executable computer programs

note.text: helpful to have understanding of programming and computer science

title.text: environmental science

note.text: is the study of the environment and the solutions of environmental problems

title.text: architecture

note.text: is both the process and the product of planning, designing, and constructing buildings and other physical structures

title.text: web development

note.text:
is a broad term for the work involved in developing a web site for the Internet (World Wide Web) or an intranet (a private network)

it can range from developing the simplest static single page of plain text to the most complex web-based internet applications, electronic businesses, and social network services

title.text: art

note.text: is a diverse range of human activities in creating visual, auditory or performing artifacts (artworks), expressing the author's imaginative or technical skill, intended to be appreciated for their beauty or emotional power

title.text: philosophy

note.text: is the study of general and fundamental problems concerning matters such as existence, knowledge, values, reason, mind, and language

title.text: sociology
